I am super grateful for the fun and awesome cooking session with Natalie @natalieportman. It was so much fun making our favorite food - Dumplings from scratch and they were so yummy.  She is truly an amazing lady with lots of great inspirations. I really appreciate her for using her platform to showcase vegan cooking, please check out her wonderful work on her page. Thank you once again, Natalie! Big hugs to you.

Here is the potsticker recipe that we made together (makes 24 potstickers). Have a beautiful weekend, everyone. Best, WoonHeng
Wrapper - 240 gram all-purpose (plain) flour, 125 ml ( ½ cup) hot water
Filling
- 14 oz (397g) firm tofu drained and pressed
- ¾ cups (75g) shredded cabbage
- 1 small carrot finely chopped
- 2 teaspoons toasted sesame oil
- 1 teaspoon salt
- A few shakes of white pepper
- A couple of handfuls of chopped spring onion and grated fresh ginger

Directions: 
To make the dumpling wrapper, place flour in a bowl and make a well in the middle. Slowly pour in the hot water. Using a spatula or a pair of chopsticks, stir to mix the flour until you get a lumpy well-mixed, or shaggy dough (if there are dry spots of flour in the bowl, add more water, 1 tablespoon at a time). Transfer it onto a cleaned surface and knead it into a rough dough. Cover with a damp towel and let it rest for about 5 mins. Then, knead the dough until a smooth top forms, about 10-12mins; rest for about 30mins.
Filling: Blanch cabbage in hot water for 45secs. Remove and quickly rinse them with cold water. Squeeze out all the liquid and give it a rough chop. Mash pressed tofu and place it into a cheesecloth bag. Wring out as much liquid as possible. Place chopped cabbage and tofu in a mixing bowl along with chopped scallions, carrots, and season with toasted sesame oil, salt, and white pepper, and ginger.
After 30 minutes, divide the dough into 24 equal portions and form them into balls. Roll each one into a thin circular wrapper. Place a filling in the middle and pleat to seal. 
Heat a non-stick pan with oil (adjust based on the size of the pan) then place the dumplings in, slightly apart in one layer. Cook over medium heat until the bottom turns golden brown.

Napa Cabbage Sticky Rice rolls '白菜糯米卷' in sweet and spicy sauce - easy flavorful comfort food made with homegrown long beans and leftover kale stems! Once wrapped, I pan-fried them and then served with a simple sauce for a delicious meal- YUM! Full detailed recipe and video are now up on my blog or check this IGTV for steps. Hope you enjoy this dish as much as I do. Have a wonderful day, friends! Best, WoonHeng

For the full recipe, steps and video, please visit: https://woonheng.com/sticky-rice-cabbage-rolls/

Ingredients
10 - 12 large Napa Cabbage leaves or other veggie of choice
oil for cooking
Cabbage Roll Sauce: 3 slices of ginger, 3-4 medium-sized mushrooms sliced, 2 tablespoons chopped green onions, 1½ tablespoons soy sauce/tamari, 1 tablespoon mirin, ½ tablespoon maple syrup (optional), 1 chopped Thai chilis (optional), salt and pepper to taste, ½ cup water, cornstarch slurry
Filling: 
1 ½ cups sticky or glutinous rice or other sticky grain such as sushi rice
1 cup water
1 cup of chopped veggies used a mixture of long beans, kale stems
1 small carrot chopped
½ tablespoon minced ginger
½ cup mushrooms, sliced used Bella
1 tablespoon soy sauce or tamari
½ tablespoon toasted sesame oil
salt and pepper to taste
Music: YouTube Audio - Faith
.

#wonton #dumpling style 2

Take one wrapper & place it on your palm like a diamond. Spoon 1 teaspoon mixture & put in the middle of wrapper. Dab some water on each end. Bring the middle two ends together, then bring right side by pushing the wrapper to the middle. Repeat for left side. Place wonton in the crease between your thumb and index finger and press to seal. Repeat until you are done with all wrapper.

This Korean-inspired 'fried' tofu😋is a must-try! All delicious flavor components in one dish - spicy, sweet, tangy - oh yes🤩!! so so good and the pickled radish (chicken mu) is the perfect pair👍🏼💕. ⁣
⁣
Full recipe and long video: https://woonheng.com/korean-fried-tofu-with-gochujang/⁣
or GOOGLE 'woonheng korean fried tofu'⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- I used frozen then thawed tofu to get the texture. But yes you can use firm tofu but please drain and press it well so the tofu's moisture will not dilute the batter⁣
- Feel free to sub the all purpose flour with gluten-free or sub rice flour with potato starch or cornstarch for a crispier texture🥰⁣
- Please check my blog for baking them - they will be less golden but taste just as great 👍🏼 ⁣
- I double air-fried these sticks to get that crispy and deeply golden brown⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try. Have a great one. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨❤️⁣⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Vegan Pad Kee Mao - Drunken noodles

node.text:
Vegan Pad Kee Mao (Drunken noodles)😋with homemade flat rice noodles is so yum and delicious.⁣
What is your favorite dish to order when you dine at a Thai restaurant? I love Pad Kee Mao and probably ate the most plates when I was in Chiangmai compared to my family😆 So, if you have some Thai basil, give this dish a try.👍🏼⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions and video:  https://woonheng.com/vegan-pad-kee-mao/⁣
⁣
or Google 'woonheng pad kee mao'⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- Store-bought fresh rice noodles come in flat sheet or precut, get the flat one so you can cut it into your desired width. ⁣
- The vegan 'fish' sauce I used is on my blog, similar to nước mắm chay and you can use my homemade vegan 'oyster' sauce (look for stir fry sauce on my blog) as well⁣
- Use your favorite leafy greens and protein - I used pan-fried tofu, yum yum😋⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try. Have a great mid week. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨❤️⁣⁣⁣⁣

Vegan Pad Woon Sen😋 for a delicious lunch at home! Do you like to serve it with rice or eat this as-is? I love it as-is,😆 so I could have more. The noodles are also known as glass noodles or fen si are made from starch, mung bean starch (similar to my liang fen ingredient) and are sold in dried form. Once it's soaked in water, it will turn white and translucent when cooked. ⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions and long video: https://woonheng.com/vegan-pad-woon-sen/⁣
or Google 'woonheng pad woon sen'⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- This recipe is inspired by Hot Thai Kitchen's YouTube🙏🏼💓⁣
- Give the noodles a few cuts with scissors before adding them to the pan⁣
- Cook in batches or use a large surface pan so you have room to move around the noodles⁣
- Have a pair of tongs or chopsticks ready when tossing the noodles - they stick quickly. You can lower the heat before adding the sauce⁣
- The noodle itself is gluten-free and I used mountain brand soy sauce (that has a gluten-free label). Please note this glass noodle is made from beans starch and not potato starch (like the Japchae).⁣⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try. Have a great start to your new week. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨❤️⁣⁣⁣

Liang Fen😋 - Jelly Noodles served cold with a deliciously tangy and spicy sauce for a refreshing meal! I've been wanting to make this dish for the longest time and kept delaying until I got the mold. It's called jelly scraper, and it looked fun to use. You don't need to use the mold though, simply cut the jelly in cubes or thin strips. 👍🏼
⁣
Full recipe instructions with long video: https://woonheng.com/liang-fen-cold-jelly-noodles/⁣
or search 'liang fen' on woonheng.com⁣
or watch it on YouTube (WoonHeng)⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- the noodles itself is made from starch and water, so it's gluten-free. It has good elasticity.⁣
- My sauce is not as light, but if you like a lighter version, add a little more water.⁣
- Try adding sesame paste or black beans in the sauce for extra layer of flavor⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try for the remaining few hot summer days.💓Have a great and safe weekend. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Meal prep - vegan Zha jiang mian

node.text:
You need this scrumptious and flavorful vegan ‘fried’ sauce noodles, ‘zha jiang mian’😋for your meals as you get back-to-routine. Made with the pleasant, mellow notes of olive from @filippoberio_us Delicato Extra Virgin Olive Oil, this sauce quickly became our family’s favorite weeknight dinners and kids' school lunches👍🏼. It’s packed with vegetables that go really well with your favorite noodles. So, if you want a tasty fuss-free meal for your busy days, save the recipe below. Don’t forget to add this extra virgin olive oil to your pantry staple too! [#AD]⁣
⁣
Ingredients:⁣
½ cup @filippoberio_us Delicato Extra Virgin Olive Oil, plus more for noodles⁣
16oz firm tofu, pressed and cubed⁣
10oz mushrooms, cleaned and cubed⁣
2 medium-sized eggplant, cubed⁣
2 tablespoon finely chopped ginger⁣
3 tablespoon chopped green onion top⁣
6 servings noodle of choice, cook as directed⁣
1-2 cups julienned carrot and cucumber⁣
Sauce:⁣
2 tablespoons sweet bean sauce⁣
1 tablespoon spicy doubanjiang⁣
1 tablespoon soy sauce⁣
½ tablespoon sugar⁣
½ teaspoon salt⁣
½ teaspoon white pepper⁣
1 tablespoon cooking wine, optional⁣
¾ cup vegetable stock⁣
⁣
Mix the sauce ingredients (except the stock) in a bowl until wel-combined.⁣
Heat a non-stick skillet with ½ cup of oil over medium heat. Add the ginger and tofu and pan-fry tofu cubes until a light yellow crust forms, flipping occasionally, 5-8 minutes. Next, sauté the mushrooms for another 3-5 minutes to brown them. Add eggplant and continue to cook for about 5-8 minutes until they turn softer. Stir in the prepared sauce and green onion tops and pour in the stock. Once the mixture comes to a boil, lower the heat to medium-low, cover the pan, and simmer for 8-10 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.⁣
While waiting, prepare the noodles as directed on the package. To prevent sticking, toss noodles with a few splashes of oil. To serve the noodles right away, mix noodles with sauce and toss with the julienned vegetables. The sauce is enough for 6-8 servings. To meal prep, place noodles in your containers, then top with vegetables and a few spoonfuls of sauce. Mix everything together before serving.

Crispy sesame balls😋, 芝麻球 (Zhī ma qiú) or Jian Dui can be easily made at home. The recipe is now live @Food52's website⁣
⁣
These balls are not only delicious but also have great meaning behind them. The way they inflate during cooking signifies prosperity. The balls rise up in the hot oil, and so this dish is often made to wish a person good luck. You’ll find sesame balls at Lunar New Year celebrations or at weddings to share happiness. Deep-frying brings out the seeds’ aroma and crunch. And glutinous (aka sweet) rice flour yields a soft, squidgy texture—plus, it’s gluten-free. ⁣
⁣
Full recipe: https://food52.com/recipes/86388-jian-dui-recipe⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- You'll only need glutinous rice flour in this recipe. I used the Thai brand version⁣
- Feel free to sub the peanut filling with mung bean or red bean paste⁣
- Please use raw white sesame seeds for this recipe⁣
⁣
I hope you give this delicious snack a try. Have a great day ahead. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨❤️⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

Miso ramen😋 is my absolute favorite. The broth is silky smooth, tasty, and slurpilicious! It brought me back all the memories from T's TanTan in Japan. I really miss that place. This recipe is suitable for the whole family, just make a big pot and it'll be a meal for everyone who loves ramen. ⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions and full video: https://woonheng.com/vegan-creamy-miso-ramen/⁣
or Google 'woonheng miso ramen' ⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- The hot bean sauce I used for this recipe was spicy but you can get a nonspicy version. ⁣
- I found that the best plant milk to use is oat, cashew, or soy - all unsweetened please. Almond is too thin.⁣
- If you don't want to make your own kombu dashi, check out my 'Cooking Tips and variations' section to see what you can sub⁣
- Sieve to get a silky-smooth broth⁣⁣
⁣
I hope you give this dish a try. Have a fantastic Monday. Stay safe and well. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣⁣⁣⁣

Rice paper nuggets in 12345 sauce😋! I don't know how many times I laughed at myself trying to say it quickly and show the fingers to fit the 30 seconds frame and got tongue twisted😂⁣
Anyway, the cooking process is really easy and the sauce is made from simple ingredients in the pantry - check what to sub on my blog.🤗💓⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions: https://woonheng.com/12345-sauce-rice-paper-nuggets/⁣
or search '12345 sauce' on woonheng.com⁣
or pin this (WoonHeng)⁣
or watch on YouTube (WoonHeng)⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- I used king oyster mushrooms - so yum⁣
- I used 6-inch diameter rice paper that I cut into half⁣
- If you can't have soy sauce, sub with coconut amino and reduce the sugar⁣
- No air fryer, try shallow pan fry the nuggets⁣
⁣
I hope you give this a try. Please keep those who got hit by the hurricane in your thoughts, thank YOU🙏🏼🙏🏼! Stay safe and well. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣⁣⁣

This vegan Nasi Lemak Bungkus is the best and most authentic way to enjoy this Malaysian iconic dish. It will bring you down memory lane as soon as you unwrap the banana leaf pack. Nasi lemak wrapped in banana leaf is the classic way to enjoy this tasty meal or sometimes known as nasi lemak bungkus (packed). It consists of a side of fried peanuts, cucumber, egg (I used vegan egg), and sambal. It cost RM0.50 a pack when I was in elementary school. Now, it’s about RM2 ($0.50). There are 2 main components in Nasi lemak: coconut rice and sambal (cooked chile paste). With these two combo and some other sides, you'll be transported to Malaysia without an air ticket. This recipe made me appreciate how convenient it is to get a pack of this tasty dish in Malaysia. The amount of time and work that goes into making this meal is truly a labor of love.🤗⁣⁣
⁣
⁣Full recipe instructions and long video: https://woonheng.com/vegan-nasi-lemak-bungkus/⁣
or google 'woonheng nasi lemak bungkus'⁣
This video shows the few important steps in making nasi lemak and the most time-consuming part is making the sambal. So, I always make a big batch and freeze them.😄
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- I made my coconut rice in a rice cooker, but you can definitely do it on the stove top⁣
- Sambal is made from a blend of fresh (if you can find red jalapeños or Fresno) and dried chiles. ⁣
- The peanuts for nasi lemak are often fried but you can use roasted ones as well.⁣
⁣
Hope you give this dish a try. Have a beautiful Thursday. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣⁣

Easy-baked Curry Potato Bun😋 - It's soft and fluffy filled with spicy potatoes that are perfect for breakfast or your afternoon treat.💗 ⁣Make some ahead to bring to lunch too.👍🏼⁣
Potatoes are delicious in any form, agree😄? They can be pan-fried, steam, baked, or used as a binder in a lot of dishes. Some of my favorite potato dishes include curry potatoes, braised potatoes with carrots, potato balls, and curry puff.⁣ So, when my comfort food mood hits, I want to make a delicious curry potato bun inspired by chicken curry buns from the bakeries in Malaysia.⁣ ⁣
⁣⁣
Full recipe instructions: https://woonheng.com/vegan-baked-curry-potato-bun/⁣
or Google 'woonheng curry potato bun'⁣
⁣⁣
Cooking notes:⁣⁣
- both bread and all-purpose flour works great in this recipe⁣⁣
- for a fluffier bread, add a pinch of baking powder⁣⁣
- okay to skip the softened butter in the dough, just be sure to knead into a soft dough with a smooth top⁣⁣
- for that glaze look, I brush it with melted vegan butter or egg wash (mix 1 tablespoon maple syrup with 2 tablespoons unsweetened oat milk) right after I took it out from the oven. Please note the skin will shrink a little if you apply too much sweet glaze. ⁣
⁣⁣
I hope you give this recipe a try. Have a great Tuesday and for those in Malaysia (Selamat Hari Merdeka). Best, WoonHeng 韵馨❤️⁣⁣

Asian-style vegan roast 'chicken'😋 (Shao Ji) made from king oyster mushroom is so succulent and tasty. The marinated tofu skin (yuba) definitely gives this dish an amazing roasted look that you can't resist having a bite. Using mushrooms as the main ingredient to create that meaty texture has been around since I was a kid. This includes mutton made from mushrooms stem, chicken satay made from lion's mane mushrooms, and many many more. This dish is often served with flavored rice (google 'woonheng char siu fan') but you can simply serve it with a side of homemade ginger garlic sauce (google 'woonheng ginger garlic sauce').⁣
⁣
Full recipe instructions with long video: https://woonheng.com/asian-style-vegan-roast-chicken/⁣
or watch it on my YouTube channel⁣
⁣
Cooking notes:⁣
- large King oyster mushrooms or trumpet (eryngii) works the best in the recipe, try to get similar size if you can⁣
- You can keep the whole stem (google 'woonheng lemon chicken') or remove the cap for other dishes⁣
- The ingredients are simple and I have the detailed steps in the video and instructions, please check it out. ⁣
⁣
I hope you give this recipe a try (inspired by Vegepapa on YouTube) and have a fantastic weekend. Best, WoonHeng 韵馨💗⁣⁣

Vegan Shanghai shao mai😋 (sticky rice dumpling), 上海烧卖 is now live @Food52 website. Shanghai shao mai have a distinct look that resembles a vase, with a round bottom, slender middle, and wide opening at the top. From the side angle, the top looks like a bouquet of flowers, don't you think?😁⁣
⁣
Recipe: https://food52.com/recipes/86331-shanghai-shao-mai-vegan-recipe ⁣
⁣⁣
Cooking notes:⁣⁣
- I used store-bought dumpling wrappers this time instead of from scratch-dough⁣
- Prepare the sticky rice as directed, I soaked mine overnight (before bed) and steamed it the next day⁣
- The wrapping method is a little different and very fun to make⁣
⁣⁣
I hope you give this dish a try. Have a great Thursday! Best, WoonHeng 韵馨⁣💜⁣⁣⁣
